City towers are now real skyscrapers (setbacks, lit windows, spire, marquee)

Replaced the flat name-boxes with proper skyscrapers: stepped setback silhouette
(three tiers narrowing upward), a grid of lit/dark windows on the main faces, a
rooftop mast with a neon beacon, and a small street-level marquee instead of a
giant name plastered across a rectangle.

